### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

forms

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Depending on the setup order, either FormGroup or FormArray disrupts the valueChanges stream of the other.

## Flowchart 
```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start] --> B{Setup Order}
    B -->|Init FormGroup with FormControl first| C[FormGroup Setup]
    B -->|Init FormArray with FormControl first| D[FormArray Setup]
    C --> E[FormArray Setup]
    D --> F[FormGroup Setup]
    E --> G{Disruption}
    F --> G{Disruption}
    G -->|FormGroup Disrupted| H[FormGroup valueChanges Stream Disrupted]
    G -->|FormArray Disrupted| I[FormArray valueChanges Stream Disrupted]
```

## Example code with both scenarios
```typescript
    if (this.mode === 'InitFormGroupWithFormControlFirst') {
      this.formGroup = new FormGroup({ formControl: this.formControl });
      this.formArray.push(this.formControl);
    } else {
      this.formArray.push(this.formControl);
      this.formGroup = new FormGroup({ formControl: this.formControl });
    }

    this.formGroup.valueChanges.subscribe((changes) =>      console.log('formGroup-valueChanges', changes)    );
    this.formArray.valueChanges.subscribe((changes) =>      console.log('formArray-valueChanges', changes)    );

   // Then trigger change on formControl
   this.formControl.setValue(Date.now());  
```

